CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 4, 1960, pg. B7 reads: "Ivy Leafs Plan Project - These "Ivies" of the Alpha Sigma Chapter of Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority are making final arrangements for their major project of the year-a picnic- which will be held at Highland Park on June 5, in honor of their "big sisters." Left to right, front row: Barbara Jones and Jude [June] Gibson.  Second row: Charmaine Austin, Ada Strong and Linda Pollard.  Third row: Judy Wise and Janice Finney.  Barbara Bryant is standing.  Not shown in picture are Rose Zimmerman and Sandy Lewis. - Harris Photo/"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of the Alpha Sigma Chapter of Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority members, from left, front row: Barbara Jones and June Gibson; second row: Charmaine Austin, Ada Strong, and Linda Pollard; third row: Judy Wise and Janice Finney; standing: Barbara Bryant, posed in interior with oriental rug, sofa, and palm leaf patterned curtains
